# Identity & Auth

## In the Gateway

- Strip client-supplied identity headers, THEN inject verified ones:

```go
identity.StripUntrusted(r.Header)
id := verify(r)        // Bearer JWT via cached JWKS, or web BFF cookie
id.Inject(r.Header)
```

- Do not fail readiness if Logto JWKS is unreachable (JWKS is cached → degrade).
- Check the Redis revocation list for sensitive operations.

## In business services

- Never parse end-user JWTs. Read identity from context:

```go
id, ok := identity.FromContext(r.Context())
```

- Enforce domain authorization (ownership, tenant isolation) locally.
- Always scope data by `id.TenantID`.

## Service-to-service

- Propagate identity + `traceparent`. The callee trusts headers only from the
  Gateway or trusted internal services (V1: network isolation + internal token;
  later: mTLS).
